If I have a span like below with no "SERVER" span, the UI will display the service name as `sample` but this makes no sense as it is a call into `mysql` from `sample`:

```
{
  ...
  "kind": "CLIENT",
  "name": "query",
  "timestamp": 1547069325788000,
  "duration": 10000,
  "localEndpoint": {
    "serviceName": "sample",
    "ipv4": "127.0.0.1",
    "port": 12345
  },
  "remoteEndpoint": {
    "serviceName": "mysql",
    "ipv4": "10.0.0.0",
    "port": 12345
  },
  "annotations": [
    {
      "timestamp": 1547069325788000,
      "value": "cs"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 1547069325798000,
      "value": "cr"
    }
  ]
}
```

This PR makes the UI use the client remote service name instead of the client local service name if no server local service name exists. I believe this fixes the leaf span issue mentioned in #2274
